      "content": "it just feels so pointless. like, if the person i built my entire life around is gone, then the life i have left isn't even really mine anymore. i look at the future and it's just a huge, dark void. i don't even want to fight to make it better because there's nothing left to fight for. it feels like the only way to actually get relief from this heaviness is to just... not be here. does that even make sense? it feels like the only logical way out.",
